Sugar production in Peru for the1986/87 season has been revised to 593,000 tonnes (raw value),down 10 pct from the previous forecast and 21 pct below the1985/86 harvest, the U.S. Agriculture Department said in itsWorld Production and Trade Report.    It said while rains in the northern mountain region areimproving the supply of irrigation water, the major benefitswill not occur until the 1987/88 season. Reuter&#3;